00:00:00.222 --> 00:00:01.930
TIMOTHY JORDAN: Hello
I'm Timothy Jordan,

00:00:01.930 --> 00:00:04.305
and this is your quick update
about the coolest developer

00:00:04.305 --> 00:00:06.760
news from Google
in the last week.

00:00:06.760 --> 00:00:09.030
The third annual Android
Security Year in Review

00:00:09.030 --> 00:00:09.859
is now available.

00:00:09.859 --> 00:00:11.400
It's a comprehensive
look at our work

00:00:11.400 --> 00:00:15.990
to protect more than 1.4 billion
Android users and their data.

00:00:15.990 --> 00:00:18.210
Take a look at the post
for a highlights, a video,

00:00:18.210 --> 00:00:20.550
and a link to the full report.

00:00:20.550 --> 00:00:23.520
The first developer preview
of Android O is now available.

00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.190
Android O introduces a number
of new features and APIs

00:00:26.190 --> 00:00:29.340
to use in your apps, including
background limits, notification

00:00:29.340 --> 00:00:32.130
channels, autofill
APIs, and more.

00:00:32.130 --> 00:00:34.287
Details and links
are on the post.

00:00:34.287 --> 00:00:36.870
Also now available is the latest
version of the Android Native

00:00:36.870 --> 00:00:39.510
Development Kit,
Android NDK r14.

00:00:39.510 --> 00:00:41.970
Updates are detailed
on the post.

00:00:41.970 --> 00:00:44.070
Chrome 58 beta is out.

00:00:44.070 --> 00:00:47.040
Updates include
IndexedDB 2.0 standard,

00:00:47.040 --> 00:00:48.930
now fully supported,
and improvement

00:00:48.930 --> 00:00:52.200
to I-frame navigation,
immersive full screen for PWA's,

00:00:52.200 --> 00:00:53.090
and more.

00:00:53.090 --> 00:00:56.160
Screen shots and
links are on the post.

00:00:56.160 --> 00:00:57.660
We recently launched
Cloud Functions

00:00:57.660 --> 00:00:59.790
for Firebase, which is a
great solution for running

00:00:59.790 --> 00:01:02.316
back-end code for
your Firebase app.

00:01:02.316 --> 00:01:04.440
These functions can be
triggered on certain events,

00:01:04.440 --> 00:01:06.120
as well as scheduled.

00:01:06.120 --> 00:01:08.430
To get started scheduling
jobs with Cloud functions

00:01:08.430 --> 00:01:10.900
for Firebase,
check out the post.

00:01:10.900 --> 00:01:12.694
Remember, sharing is caring.

00:01:12.694 --> 00:01:14.860
I'm with Timothy Jordan,
and I'll see you next week.

